## 5. Reactivation Frequency Estimate

### 5.1 Physical Timescales

For self-gravitating systems:

**Crossing time:**
```
t_cross ~ R / σ
```

where R = system radius, σ = velocity dispersion

**Relaxation time:**
```
t_relax ~ (N / ln N) × t_cross
```

**Core collapse time:**
```
t_cc ~ 15 × t_relax
```

### 5.2 Expected Reactivation Rate

Phase transitions occur when:
- Binaries form or dissolve (~ t_relax)
- Core undergoes collapse (~ t_cc)
- Massive particles segregate (~ 0.1 t_relax)
- Escape events (~ 0.01 t_relax for high-velocity stars)

**Order-of-magnitude estimate:**
```
R ~ N_events × (t_sim / t_event)
```

For globular cluster with N ~ 10⁵ over t_sim ~ 10¹⁰ yr:
- t_cross ~ 10⁵ yr
- t_relax ~ 10⁹ yr
- t_sim / t_relax ~ 10

**Expected:** R ~ 10² - 10³ reactivations over lifetime

**Verification:** Run algorithm on test system, count actual R

